I did not try the breakfast, since it was rather expensive (17.50 euro), and there were nice bakeries right around the corner.	I didn't try breakfast and I thought having to pay 5 Euros (per day) for a basic tea/coffee facility in the room was rather odd, but maybe that's the way things are done here.	However, you could book this facility for 5 Euros a day, which is very good value when a cup of coffee averages 3 Euros in local cafes.	I would not say that either of these options were good value for money, but Amsterdam did seem particulalrly expensive compared with others I have visited.